Listening to the right music can enhance flavours in food and drink . 
  Luciano Pavarotti singing Nessun Dorma can enhance the bitterness in coffee and the intensity of a chocolate mousse . 
  Oxford University psychologists say music can bring out sweet, salty and bitter flavours in a range of foods . 
  The right music also enhances the taste of wine by 15 per cent . 
 